{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Plan-review advisory dispositions (v3 PASS, 0 blocking, 20 advisory). The advisories are specification-precision refinements; the material ones are ACCEPTED and will be reflected in the implementation (and in the test oracle) before the change receives its Gerrit votes:\n- ACCEPT (evidence pipeline, ~0.67/0.33): the consolidation job + fragment names (evidence-shapin/evidence-build/evidence-mcp) are specified concretely — a final 'consolidate-evidence' job that needs: the fragment-producing jobs, downloads all evidence-* artifacts, and concatenates them into release-evidence.txt; test_release_workflow_pins.py check (f) asserts the fragment names + their write commands + the consolidation job's download/concat wiring.\n- ACCEPT (check_build_env_locked base allowlist, ~0.67/0.54): the allowlist is exactly {pip, setuptools, wheel} (lowercased), documented as a constant in the script with a comment; the script fails on any installed pkg absent from the lock OR version-mismatched, EXCEPT those three; unit test feeds a clean fixture (passes) and an extra-package fixture (fails).\n- ACCEPT (actionlint install, ~0.54/0.26): actionlint is installed in a Makefile prerequisite via a pinned-version GitHub release download + sha256sum -c against a hard-coded digest (dogfooding the same digest-verify discipline), pinned to a specific actionlint version; the Makefile target is idempotent (skips if the pinned binary is already present).\n- REJECT (0.40 generic 'AC/DoD quality'): too vague to action; the ACs are concrete + test-backed after the two BLOCK remediations.\nRemaining lower-impact advisories are consistency/wording notes folded into the same concrete specifications above."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784139732734059001,"uuid":"96ea32f2-0a15-4ae4-94cf-7e5a8b21f985"}